<doc>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_MODE">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines at what times a transform in a topology is drained.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/mf-toponode-drain-attribute">MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/media-foundation-enumerations">Media Foundation Enumerations</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_DEFAULT">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is drained when the end of a stream is reached. It is not drained when markout is reached at the end of a segment.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_ALWAYS">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is drained whenever a topology ends.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_MODE.MF_TOPONODE_DRAIN_NEVER">
    <summary>
      <para>The transform is never drained.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>